          "content": "Strategic IT management involves aligning technological solutions with business goals. **Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP)** systems integrate core business processes, such as finance, HR, and supply chain management, into unified platforms. This streamlines operations, improves data accuracy, and enhances decision-making.\n\nAdditionally, **IT Governance** ensures that IT investments deliver value and mitigate risks through frameworks like COBIT and ITIL. Effective governance requires collaboration between IT leaders and business executives, establishing clear policies, performance metrics, and compliance standards.\n\nAnother critical area is **Cybersecurity Strategy**, which involves not just technical defenses but also organizational policies, employee training, and proactive risk assessments.\n\nQuestion: What is a primary benefit of implementing an ERP system in an organization?",
